{
  "text": "The impact of hypomagnesemia in patients undergoing anti-EGFR treatment for mCRC has been underestimated, most likely because magnesium levels are rarely measured during routine screening [CITATION_1] . Patients' electrolytes should be periodically monitored during -and for eight weeks after -the completion of anti-EGFR therapy. Hypomagnesemia should be suspected in mCRC patients being treated with cetuximab or panitumumab who present with chronic diarrhea, hypocalcemia, refractory hypokalemia, and ventricular arrhythmia [CITATION_2] .",
  "correct_citation": {
